<title>USA: Systems&amp;Computer to redeem convertible debt.</title>
<headline>Systems&amp;Computer to redeem convertible debt.</headline>
<dateline>MALVERN, Pa. 1997-04-09</dateline>
<text>
<p>Systems &amp; Computer Technology Corp on Wednesday said it called for redemption all of its outstanding 6-1/4 percent convertible subordinated debentures due 2003.</p>
<p>The redemption date will be May 9, 1997.</p>
<p>As of April 8, 1997, the principal amount of debentures outstanding was $27.3 million. The redemption price, which includes premium and accrued and unpaid interest from March 1, 1997, is $1,053.62 for each $1,000 principal amount of debentures surrendered for redemption.</p>
</text>
